## Annotation Format

Every reversed `.c` file starts with:

```c
// FUNCTION: {target_name} 0x<virtual_address>
// STATUS: STUB
// ORIGIN: GAME
// SIZE: <bytes>

void __cdecl function_name(void)
{{
    // stub
}}
```

The function name and symbol are derived automatically from the C function definition.
`CFLAGS` is optional — falls back to the target default from `rebrew-project.toml`.

**STATUS**: `EXACT` (byte-perfect) > `RELOC` (match after masking relocations)
> `MATCHING` (close) > `STUB` (incomplete)

